The article announces several nominations and appointments. Derek Kan, currently the Executive Associate Director of the Office of Management and Budget in the Executive Office of the President, is nominated to be the Deputy Director of the Office of Management and Budget. He has previous experience as the Under Secretary of Transportation for Policy and as a General Manager for Lyft in Southern California.

Michael A. McCarthy, currently serving as Consul General of the United States Consulate General in Johannesburg, South Africa, is nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Liberia. He has previous experience in various roles within the State Department, including as the Office Director for the Office of Retirement.

Lucas N. Polakowski is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Defense for Nuclear, Chemical, and Biological Defense Programs. He has experience as the Managing Member of Everest Technology, LLC, a national security consulting firm, and has served in the United States Army for over 36 years in various defense-related roles.

Melvyn Evans Huff is nominated to be a Member of the National Science Board for a term of six years. No further information is provided about his background or qualifications.